 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4625/i3-status-bar-not-showing-my-battery/?answer=4630#post-id-4630</link><description>This is the same problem I had with Ubuntu 14.04. Changing the battery number in the `i3status.conf` file from 0 to 1 helped me.

When you do this, you have to change two lines. First near the top of the configuration.

    # order += "battery 0" old
    order += "battery 1" # new

And the following, somewhere in the middle:

    # battery 0 { old
    battery 1 { # new</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Sep 2014 13:01:10 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4625/i3-status-bar-not-showing-my-battery/?answer=4630#post-id-4630</guid></item></channel></rss>